# Type Safety (Strict)

- **Zero Tolerance for `any`:** Never use `any`. Use generics, `unknown`, or define specific interfaces/types.
- **Zod Integration:** Use Zod for all data validation — API responses, form schemas, and external input.

```ts
// ❌ BAD
function parse(data: any) { ... }

// ✅ GOOD
const schema = z.object({ name: z.string() });
function parse(data: unknown) {
  return schema.parse(data);
}
```
